<treatment id="227087A8355FB85DFF558FD1FA487A13" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524179" ID-GBIF-Taxon="195195087" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6524179" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:227087A8355FB85DFF558FD1FA487A13" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/227087A8355FB85DFF558FD1FA487A13" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<subSubSection id="E2C36535355FB85DFF558FD1FC5579EF" box="[151,896,151,178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558FD1FC5579EF" blockId="17.[151,896,151,178]" box="[151,896,151,178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<heading id="F12E81D2355FB85DFF558FD1FC5579EF" bold="true" box="[151,896,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" reason="1">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFF558FD1FC5579EF" bold="true" box="[151,896,151,178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
An identification key to the males of Indian 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFD7E8FD1FC5579EF" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1907" box="[700,896,151,178]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFD7E8FD1FC5579EF" bold="true" box="[700,896,151,178]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">Burmagomphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2C36535355FB85DFF558FA6FD7A78F0" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558FA6FD7A78F0" blockId="17.[151,1437,223,430]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
In his identification key to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFDF58F99FC5879A4" authority=", Fraser (1934)" authorityName=", Fraser" authorityYear="1934" box="[567,909,223,250]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFDF58F99FD3D79A4" box="[567,744,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">Burmagomphus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CE484B4F355FB85DFD348FA6FC5879A4" author="Fraser, F. C." box="[758,909,223,250]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" refId="ref5704" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1934) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Odonata. Vol. II. Taylor and Francis, London, 398 pp." type="book" year="1934">Fraser (1934)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
wrote: “Humeral stripe a short lower one only, without any upper spot”. This is true of other known species, but the presence of the upper humeral spot is known to be variable within the species of 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFDFF8E61FD3B781C" authorityName=", Fraser" authorityYear="1934" box="[573,750,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFDFF8E61FD3B781C" box="[573,750,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">Burmagomphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="CE484B4F355FB85DFCFE8E61FC36781C" author="Kosterin, O. E." box="[828,995,295,321]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6039" refString="Kosterin, O. E. (2014) Notes on intraspecific variation of some Gomphidae (Odonata) species in Cambodia. IDF Report, 68, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="2014">Kosterin 2014</bibRefCitation>
), this is also true for 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFB208E6EFA43781C" authorityName="Joshi &amp; Sawant &amp; Ogale &amp; Kunte" authorityYear="2022" box="[1250,1430,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaukulensis">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFB208E6EFA43781C" box="[1250,1430,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. chaukulensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFED38E0AFE7D7838" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1926" box="[273,424,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cauvericus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFED38E0AFE7D7838" box="[273,424,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. cauvericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be better diagnosed based upon the lateral thoracic markings and the shape of posterior hamuli. We provide below an updated key to the males of 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFCE18E29FCBE78D4" box="[803,875,367,393]" class="Aves" family="Phasianidae" genus="Indian" kingdom="Animalia" order="Galliformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="413" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Indian</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFCB08E29FBF678D4" authorityName=", Fraser" authorityYear="1934" box="[882,1059,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFCB08E29FBF678D4" box="[882,1059,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">Burmagomphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on inspection of additional material and the description of our new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2C36535355FB85DFF558E9EFA487A13" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" type="key">
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558E9EFA4978B0" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,472,494]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFF558E9EFF7F78B0" bold="true" box="[151,170,472,493]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">1.</emphasis>
Dorsal and antehumeral stripes fused..................................................................... 
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFA528E9EFA4978B0" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,472,493]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">2</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558EB0FA497B57" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,501,523]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
- Dorsal and antehumeral stripes not fused, antehumeral stripe short or absent...................................... 
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFA528EB3FA497B57" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,501,522]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">4</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558D55FA497B75" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,530,553]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
- Antehumeral stripe broad and long, running parallel to the dorsal thoracic stripe........................ 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFACD8D55FA497B75" authorityName="Laidlaw" authorityYear="1922" box="[1295,1436,530,552]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sivalikensis">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFACD8D55FA497B75" bold="true" box="[1295,1436,530,552]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. sivalikensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558D76FA497B1B" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,560,582]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFF558D76FF7C7B18" bold="true" box="[151,169,560,581]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">2.</emphasis>
Thoracic collar fused, S8 yellow with a dorsal black patch......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFACE8D76FA497B1B" authorityName="Laidlaw" authorityYear="1922" box="[1292,1436,560,582]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyramidalis">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFACE8D76FA497B1B" bold="true" box="[1292,1436,560,582]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. pyramidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558D08FA497B3F" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,589,611]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
- Thoracic collar interrupted medially, S8 black or with minute yellow markings.................................... 
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFA528D0BFA497B3F" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,589,610]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">3</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558D2DFA497BDD" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,618,641]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFF558D2DFF7C7BDD" bold="true" box="[151,169,619,640]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">3.</emphasis>
Cerci with two sharp spines on lateral margin, paraproct sharply extended laterally...................... 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFAD18D2DFA497BDD" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1924" box="[1299,1436,618,640]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divaricatus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFAD18D2DFA497BDD" bold="true" box="[1299,1436,618,640]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. divaricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558DCEFA497BC3" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,648,670]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
- Cerci with two blunt spines on lateral margin, paraproct not extended laterally......................... 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFAC58DCEFA497BC3" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1924" box="[1287,1436,648,670]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hasimaricus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFAC58DCEFA497BC3" bold="true" box="[1287,1436,648,670]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. hasimaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558DE3FA487BE7" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1437,677,699]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFF558DE3FF7C7BE7" bold="true" box="[151,169,677,698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">4.</emphasis>
Thoracic stripes on mesepimeron and metepisternum broad and fused................................. 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFAD48DE0FA487BE7" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1926" box="[1302,1437,677,699]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cauvericus">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFAD48DE0FA487BE7" bold="true" box="[1302,1437,677,699]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. cauvericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558D85FA497B85" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" box="[151,1436,707,729]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
- Thoracic stripes on mesepimeron and metepisternum parallel and separated...................................... 
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFA528D85FA497B85" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,707,728]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">5</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558DA6FA487A4E" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFF558DA6FF7C7BA8" bold="true" box="[151,169,736,757]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">5.</emphasis>
Stripe on mesepisternum broad, posterior hamuli with one spine at each side, cerci inwardly curved with an inconspicuous lateral expansion.............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFAF08DB8FA487A4E" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1924" box="[1330,1437,765,787]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laidlawi">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFAF08DB8FA487A4E" bold="true" box="[1330,1437,765,787]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. laidlawi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA6636BE355FB85DFF558C5DFA487A13" blockId="17.[151,1437,472,846]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFF558C5DFF4A7A6D" bold="true" box="[151,159,795,816]" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">-</emphasis>
Stripe on mesepisternum pointed anteriorly, posterior hamuli very wide with a curved spine at anterior end and variable number of spines at posterior end, cerci pointed at apices with a prominent lateral expansion ending in a spine..... 
<taxonomicName id="6DD94D3D355FB85DFB3C8C7EFA487A13" authorityName="Joshi &amp; Sawant &amp; Ogale &amp; Kunte" authorityYear="2022" box="[1278,1437,824,846]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Burmagomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaukulensis">
<emphasis id="98ADEAAC355FB85DFB3C8C7EFA487A13" bold="true" box="[1278,1437,824,846]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="430">B. chaukulensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
